<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Legation in Austria</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d785</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">785</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-07-17T14:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-07-17T14:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Austria)/7–1748:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Legation in Austria</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-17T15:00:00-04:00">July 17, 1948—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>641. Sov note on Berlin<note n="1" xml:id="d785fn1">The Soviet note of July 14 is
                        printed <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_960">p.
                        960</ref>.</note> refers twice to Vienna and international agreements
                    concerning Austria, linking Austria with Germany in justifying Sov blockade. We
                    would appreciate your evaluation of these references and your analysis of
                    possible basis for a blockade of Vienna. Although possible Sov action would
                    undoubtedly be based on legal position and charge of violation of international
                    agreements by western states, could such instances as Sov complaints reported in
                    SO–15417 <pb facs="1462" n="1428" xml:id="pg_1428"/> July 15<note n="2" xml:id="d785fn2">Not found in Department files.</note> on air transport
                    difficulties (<gloss target="#t_P1">P</gloss>–2117 July 14<note n="2" xml:id="d785fn3">Not found in Department files.</note>) be utilized by Sovs
                    as cause for aggressive action?</p>
                <p>If you consider Sov blockade likely, Dept requests your and <persName corresp="#p_KLGG1">Keyes</persName>’ recommendations for counter-action and
                    for steps which might be taken to forestall or delay such a move.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
